getLevelNumber().Description: Returns the number for this level, e.g. "level 10". This is the level that this object represents. For a player to be considered as being of this level, the value given by @B_com#google#android#gms#games#PlayerLevelInfo#getCurrentXpTotal_E@ must fall in the range [@B_com#google#android#gms#games#PlayerLevel#getMinXp_E@, @B_com#google#android#gms#games#PlayerLevel#getMaxXp_E@).

ClassDesc: Data object representing a level a player can obtain in the metagame. A PlayerLevel has three components: a numeric value, and a range of XP totals it represents. A player is considered a given level if they have getMinXp() and getMaxXp().
